[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering processor loading**\n\nI'm thinking through how processor classes are loaded via _procLoader from processorpath. If the processorpath is set to the current classpath, it seems like EclipseFileManager might create a URLClassLoader. This situation could result in loading another copy of the test class, which could lead to static flags in the test class not being the same as those loaded by JUnit. That sounds like a potential issue to watch out for!\n\n**Evaluating test compilation**\n\nI’m thinking about the existing test that uses the classpath option. It seems that if I'm compiling source that references a test annotation class in a native context, it might not work as expected. Those annotation processor fixtures depend on nested annotations present in the test class. I wonder if the existing test passed because the java.class.path property is set to include the test native image. It feels like there’s a lot to consider here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a92bb1da5926a480169f0e85c0d988193902c2cc73ed3e2c7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8OhvKUDJMS2eP4_P19JTh9TCQGrOPeQxOllZTW7GCbmtZLFsvMQ_UHWONtL0d2UKJ-ywxea_IqXe4Nfpp54o2MYXYSP5JsdvPEcTrKLzdjoWrIZiY3r1GftUi7T0-GN42JcUAVQwYEIJravurciTisix37a7CdQah9xpxq56Uy_mWtIrFber902hvGP4B0FQArCJEWwtIV68rMmsDg2CGHsXiuJTxcCOdtnQ3SSh20aKahW7_kbp_BUeO3mFNRrER2y_W3WMpdthIp4a8ZuAmxrhHZ7CedEQXlu8PioqmWSwL5CoNEHtrjeOL0kbDCjj53GsjMYtgatxA10kix_y391GNFCul2LtOsn-lx4AtIaWZT40ViKY-W8Aqn426N1WIHyRkgAZKPB_GA9znD_3bvLAjrlZaXV-rlFZYJPcJ5SQ7BZiMK91uB0-cu-j4M3Yd4zxwcVH6VORIxdXZzE3OuEN88GOLgE9piS3zqg8CykpaKdPlUzFlXB-1OTP4PP_NeyJt3qphr7n_FPD4VEvXqE5HdFY8cPMi1l9XBYDciolSPHo5bVtC0kSzRMGoao91g2OP4LxZhMBVLykeF-690eF4M4rCV7geNd5wg2QtPLjCzwwHwVQ6sJnPGEzl5sec7KmasEG4xarjyFWm-DFqNyZzCoNtLjRfh4P12xi4B2x9q0gFXAhFguKbVyUh6mMExiSybmfAaKQ_OEIGUyTSkhlbYA0bj6fqeabykOBEFlkhRWtU2mFfVkdCHzq2s5dl9Fwql_L_WdWSAOX41_XaqGOL